byline.original: By MICHAEL M. GRYNBAUM and THOMAS KAPLAN

abstract: New York Gov Andrew M Cuomo and New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio emerge disappointed and diminished following anemic legislative session; prolonged acrimony between men has held them back from reaching policy goals, even those like higher wages and immigrants' rights that they hold in common.
lead_paragraph: Two different personalities, conflict-based and conflict-averse, were unable to find common ground on major goals, and lawmakers are adjourning with each man looking diminished.

headline.main: Cuomo and de Blasio’s Feud Is a Factor in an Anemic Legislative Session
headline.print_headline: Cuomo-de Blasio Feud Is a Factor in an Anemic Legislative Session
